title: Dalton State Volleyball Scores Win
text: Tuesday, October 20 2015, 10:15 PM EDT Dalton State Volleyball Scores Win DS Volleyball Takes Truett-McConnell, The Dalton State volleyball team (10-10overall, 4-6 SSAC) ran their win streak to three Tuesday night with a straightset victory over visiting Truett-McConnell at Bandy Gymnasium. The Roadrunners dominated the firstset, breaking open a close 16-15 battle by scoring nine of the final 10 pointsand win it 25-17. The second set wasclose through a 20-20 tie, but DS pulled out the 25-21 set win. The Roadrunners never trailed in thethird set, but the visitors never gave up. The match was tied at 23, but DaltonState finished off the set, 25-23. Kianna Delaney led Dalton State with 17points and 15 kills, two blocked shots and six digs. Anna Metzler had sevenkills and a dozen digs. Savannah Nelson had six kills and one blocked shot.Metzler and Nelson each scored 7.5 points. Michala Askew had 35 assists. OliviaKeegan had 10 digs.
